rComments: Super Prof. Lots of writing, but well worth it in the end.

I took her class in first year, and she inspired me to switch my major to Religion. LOVED her lectures, readings, film choices - everything. When I saw her again in my fourth year, she remembered me three years later! Sarah is a fantastic professor, take her class if you can.

When she says that she wants you to do well, she means it. She's incredibly approachable and encourages you to get help outside of class. You will definitely grow as a writer and critical thinker in her class!! She's a very good teacher and incredibly enthusiastic! Loved her! :)
Enthusiastic professor. I enjoyed listening to her lectures. The course is heavy on essays to improve your writing moving forward. Great class.

One of the best professors I ever had! She is very helpful, encouraging and insightful. I passed the class with an amazing   grade while I initially believed I wouldn't do very well. If I have another chance to take a class taught by her I will!!

Sarah is one of the best instructors at U of T.  She has a wonderful sense of humour, and can deal with tough topics professionally.  She is very easy to approach, she wants to help you succeed.  Unequivocally one of the best experiences I had at U of T.  Take any course she teaches, you will LOVE her.

Can't say enough good things about Sarah. Superb thought provoking course; fun, easy-going, very clear, prof approachable outside of class, and very democratic: weighed down the test claiming she doesn't believe in them ("NEITHER DO WE!" thought everyone in class), and polled us on topics of interest for the test. Best class this semester
